{"id":14880946,"mediaExerciseId":"7f91a530-47d3-43a5-97c5-f5a5067acfad","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":184,"solutions":[{"id":5967252,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will determine the amount of payment required to have $60,000 in our savings account after 12 years with an interest of 6.4%.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"To determine the amount of payments to pay each period, we will use the spreadsheet function PMT. The PMT function calculates the amount of payments required on loans based on the interest rates and regular payments.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The spreadsheet PMT function formula is as follows:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nPMT&=(rate, nper,pv,[fv],[type]) \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\n$rate$, which refers to the interest rate\n\n$nper$, represent the period\n\n$pv$, which means the present value\n\n$[Fv]$, which refers to the future value\n\n$[type]$, which indicates the period basis of the computation\n \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e6c7e3525040afc8bd766afde4a5cd7f/27824229b1534245da4941f606d4b900/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e6c7e3525040afc8bd766afde4a5cd7f/27824229b1534245da4941f606d4b900/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"In calculating the loan payment using the PMT function, we will consider the following details from the problem.\n\n| Particulars   |          |\n|---------------|----------|\n| Interest rate | 6.4%     |\n| Period        | 12        |\n| Present value | $60,000  |","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":350,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e6c7e3525040afc8bd766afde4a5cd7f/fce7242d1e47f9a6416c9758724e24e4/lateximg_large.png","width":780},"regular":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e6c7e3525040afc8bd766afde4a5cd7f/fce7242d1e47f9a6416c9758724e24e4/lateximg.png","width":392}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Since our computation focuses on the required repayment, the future value or FV in the PMT function should be zero, and the type is also zero, which indicates an end-of-year basis. Please note that the future value amount should be negative for the function to work correctly","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now calculate the amount of deposit required.\n\n!['slader'](https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/04e4663b-5142-4354-8cd9-8f9b5d41acc4-1640887709810871.png)\n\n\n**Therefore based on our calculation, the payment amount to obtain the $60,000 after 12 years is $3,515.30.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e6c7e3525040afc8bd766afde4a5cd7f/1e0c45bcd6d1429b6859c2919e2f82db/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e6c7e3525040afc8bd766afde4a5cd7f/1e0c45bcd6d1429b6859c2919e2f82db/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"1f603a90-c33c-4eb1-b07e-941710601f29","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"aut